I agree on quite a lot.  An OS is just the base, but people don't use OS's
they use the applications.  As a result, key applications are very important
for OS/2.  Unfortunately, the key apps for OS/2 I havne't heard about outside
the Internet.  Mesa sounds like one hell of a spreadsheet, but I haven't heard
of it.  Describe is one heck of a Word Processor.  Lotus releases apps for OS/2
which so far are poor Windoze ports, but are getting better, and I believe 
Lotus has a commitment.  cc:Mail works great under OS/2.  IBM's dictation
and speech recognition are incredible, and enhanced by OS/2's capaiblity.  

I still think it runs windows better than Win 3.11 does.  I see crashes and 
a lot of programs that don't work well under Windows, work much better under
OS/2.  Also, I am acutally able to work and multi-task windows applications 
under OS/2.  I have found that multiple Windows applications under a single
VDM multitask better than under Win 3.11!  And I am able to work more 
efficiently because of it.  So to that, I disagree.

The apps are there, the OS is there, the capability is there, it just needs
to grow!  Unfortunately, I feel like the only person in my group of friends
and relations promoting OS/2!  I could use a little help!

